"# Fix Entity Balances due to Supabase Query Limits

## Goal Description

The database table `daily_cash_operations` contains more than 1000 rows (currently 1010 rows). Supabase's default limit for a `.select()` query is 1000 rows.
Because the queries for fetching all operations inside `fetchData` and `handleBackupData` were not paginated, only the 1000 newest operations were being fetched. The 10 oldest operations (including starting balances and early transactions) were omitted, which corrupted the balance calculations of entities like `ASSOCIATION SIRAJ` (showing `4900 MAD` instead of `0 MAD`).

The proposed solution is to implement an asynchronous paginated helper function `fetchAllOperations` in `DailyCashTracking.jsx` and use it to retrieve all operations in chunks of 1000, ensuring complete datasets are used for calculations and exports.

## Proposed Changes

### Daily Cash Tracking Component

#### [MODIFY] [DailyCashTracking.jsx](file:///Users/ly/Desktop/antigravity%20project/suivi-ca-app/src/components/DailyCashTracking.jsx)

