"# Implementation Plan - Global Pagination Fix for 1000-Row Limit

## Goal Description
Supabase REST API queries are capped at a maximum of 1000 records per select query by default. To prevent silent truncation of database records, we will implement paginated queries (recursive fetch looping using range offsets) across all components that fetch transaction-based records without date bounds or across wide periods.

Specifically, we will update:
1. **Backup Utility (`backupUtils.js`)**: Paginate all table fetches so backup exports are complete.
2. **Sales Component (`Sales.jsx`)**: Paginate general sales and fuel sales queries.
3. **Operating Expenses Component (`OperatingExpenses.jsx`)**: Paginate operating expenses, fuel prices list, and margin/EBIT calculation queries.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backup Utility

#### [MODIFY] [backupUtils.js](file:///Users/ly/Desktop/antigravity%20project/suivi-ca-app/src/utils/backupUtils.js)
Replace standard fetches in `fetchAllData` with a paginated helper `fetchTableAllRows`:
```javascript
const fetchTableAllRows = async (table) => {
    let allData = [];
    let page = 0;
    const pageSize = 1000;
    while (true) {
        const { data, error } = await supabase
            .from(table)
            .select('*')
            .range(page * pageSize, (page + 1) * pageSize - 1);

        if (error) throw error;
        if (!data || data.length === 0) break;
        allData.push(...data);
        if (data.length < pageSize) break;
        page++;
    }
    return allData;
};
```

---

### 2. Sales Component

#### [MODIFY] [Sales.jsx](file:///Users/ly/Desktop/antigravity%20project/suivi-ca-app/src/components/Sales.jsx)
Modify `fetchSales` and `fetchFuelSales` to load all records page-by-page by appending `.range()` inside a loop.

